'''Nishida Nagao''' (にしだ ながお, [[1909]][[3月31日]] – [[1981]][[3月28日]]) was a Japanese {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|12=draft|12=draft}} scholar and Honorary {{ill|Professor|ja|教授|12=draft|12=draft}} at {{ill|Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大學|12=draft|12=draft}}.
A native of {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|12=draft|12=draft}}, he graduated from {{ill|Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大學|12=draft|12=draft}} and studied under {{ill|Miyaji Naoki|ja|宮地直一|12=draft|12=draft}}. Before World War II, he worked as a researcher at the {{ill|Ōkura Seishin Bunka Kenkyūjo|ja|大倉精神文化研究所|12=draft|12=draft}} and as a lecturer at {{ill|Tokyo Imperial University|ja|東京帝国大学|12=draft|12=draft}}; after the war, he served as a professor at {{ill|Kokugakuin University|ja|國學院大學|12=draft|12=draft}}. In 1955, with his paper “A Preliminary Discussion on the Origin of Japanese Religions” (『日本宗教の発生に関する一試論』), he was awarded a Doctorate in Literature by Kokugakuin University.
== Works == * ''{{ill|Hagakure Lectures|ja|葉隠講話|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Yūseido Publishing, 1942 * ''{{ill|Studies in Shinto History|ja|神道史の研究|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – {{ill|Yuzankaku|ja|雄山閣|12=draft|12=draft}}, 1943 * ''{{ill|On Shinto Theory|ja|神道論|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Bulletin of the Kōkōkai/Ōkura Seishin Bunka Kenkyūjo, 1943 * ''{{ill|Gods and the State|ja|神々と国家|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Meiseidō, 1944 * ''{{ill|Historical Studies of Japanese Classics|ja|日本古典の史的研究|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Risōsha, 1956 * ''{{ill|Studies in the History of Japanese Religious Thought|ja|日本宗教思想史の研究|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Risōsha, 1956 * ''{{ill|Studies in Shinto History, Vol. 2|ja|神道史の研究 第2|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Risōsha, 1957 * ''{{ill|Peripheral Aspects of Ancient Literature|ja|古代文学の周辺|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Nanmundō/Sakura Fūsha, 1964 * ''{{ill|Historical Studies of Shrines|ja|神社の歴史的研究|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Hanawa Shobō, 1966 * ''{{ill|Studies in Japanese Shinto History|ja|日本神道史研究|12=draft|12=draft}}'' (10 volumes) – Kōdansa, 1978–79 : Volume 1: General Introduction : Volumes 2–3: Ancient Period : Volumes 4–5: Medieval Period : Volumes 6–7: Early Modern Period : Volumes 8–9: Studies on Shrines : Volume 10: Classics
== Co-authored Works == * ''{{ill|The Cosmic Aspect of Shinto: Seeking Planetary Nostalgia in the Cosmogram of the Soul|ja|神道の宇宙 魂のコスモグラムに遊星的郷愁を求めて|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – co-authored with {{ill|Takahashi Hidemoto|ja|高橋秀元|12=draft|12=draft}}, Kōsōsha, 1980 (Planetary Books) * ''{{ill|The Original Shadows of the Gods|ja|神々の原影|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – co-authored with {{ill|Mitsuhashi Ken|ja|三橋健|12=draft|12=draft}}, Heikawa Shuppan, 1983
== Edited Works == * Edited {{ill|Ooyama Tameki|ja|大山為起|12=draft|12=draft}}’s ''{{ill|Shizoku Mokan, Vol. 22|ja|氏族母鑑 22巻|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – {{ill|Fushimi Inari Taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社|12=draft|12=draft}}, 1957 * ''{{ill|Nakatomi no Momo / Nakatomi Momo-shō|ja|中臣秡・中臣秡抄|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Sōbunsha, 1977 (Yoshida Sōsho)
== Commemorative Essay Collection == * ''{{ill|Collected Essays in Memory of Dr. Nishida Nagao on Shinto and Shinto History|ja|神道及び神道史 西田長男博士追悼論文集|12=draft|12=draft}}'' – Edited by the Kokugakuin University Shinto History Society, Meicho Fukyūkai, 1987
